               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; names of the donors (or owners);&#xD;
incipit of prayers and hymns (sometimes only one word); &#xD;
some other words (or their abbreviation), e.g., sälam (e.g., fol. 51v), lä-ṭǝbuʿ (e.g., fol. 52v), ʾafṭunä (e.g., fol. 33v); elements of the punctuation signs and the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- About the text “Mäṣḥafä Säʿatat” and the different versions, cp. EAE V,<ref type="mss" corresp="ES501503">501-503</ref>. The text in Ms.<ref type="mss" corresp="ESqmm003">QMM-003</ref>seems to belong to the category described as S.2.</note>
                     <note>- The text is very similar to Ms.<ref type="mss" corresp="ESmr027">MR-027</ref>.</note>
                     <note>- The Ms. contains most of the prayers and hymns of the edition Mäṣḥafä Säʿatat, bä-gǝˤǝzǝnna bä-ʾamarǝñña. Zä-lelit wä-zä-nägh, Addis Abäba 1952 A.M. [1960 A.D.].</note>
                     <note>A similar text is contained in Ms. EMML 2096, fols.<ref type="mss" corresp="ES84r125">84r-125</ref>v.</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
